{"id":"highland-scenic-highway","generatedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z","designation":"National Scenic Byway","parkCode":null,"source":{"roadArticle":"West Virginia Route 150","revisionId":1288192292,"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Virginia_Route_150"},"attribution":{"license":"CC BY-SA 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/","articleUrl":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Virginia_Route_150","text":"Route, junction, and history details adapted from the Wikipedia article \"West Virginia Route 150\", by Wikipedia contributors, licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0."},"sources":[{"name":"Wikipedia","src":"wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Virginia_Route_150","revisionId":1288192292,"retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"},{"name":"Federal Highway Administration — National Scenic Byways","src":"fhwa","url":"https://www.fhwa.dot.gov/byways","retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"},{"name":"OpenStreetMap contributors (ODbL)","src":"osm","url":"https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright","retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"}],"endpoints":null,"itinerary":[{"place":"West Virginia Route 150 (start)","mileFromStart":0,"kind":"terminus","lat":38.3067,"lng":-80.09436,"seq":1,"src":"openstreetmap","control":[],"note":"The drive begins here","toNextMi":5.7},{"place":"Little Laurel Overlook","mileFromStart":5.7,"kind":"overlook","lat":38.34018,"lng":-80.16398,"seq":2,"src":"openstreetmap","control":[],"note":"","toNextMi":7.6},{"place":"West Virginia Route 150 (end)","mileFromStart":13.3,"kind":"terminus","lat":38.28216,"lng":-80.23755,"seq":3,"src":"openstreetmap","control":[],"note":"The drive ends here"}],"history":{"paragraphs":["WV 150 is designated as the parkway portion of the Highland Scenic Highway. Dedicated in 1980, the road is specially designed to be a scenic byway with a meandering course along mountain ridges that reach an elevation of 4,545 feet (1,385 m). Due to these geographical conditions, the road is not maintained in the winter months. (Access is not prevented during the winter, however.) Furthermore, commercial traffic is prohibited and the speed limit is 45 miles per hour (72 km/h).","The parkway section provides several scenic overlooks of Cranberry Glades and the Cranberry Wilderness to the west and of the Ridge-and-valley Appalachians to the east, from numerous points along the Allegheny Front. The overlook at Black Mountain also provides an educational boardwalk that explains the irresponsible timbering practices that led to a destructive forest fire that left the area barren for decades.","The parkway also provides access to recreational areas along the Williams River and to several different trails with varying degrees of difficulty. The road is not plowed during the winter and commonly sees significant snow accumulations at its high elevation. It is frequently used for snowmobiling and cross-country skiing in these conditions."],"sourceSection":"Route description","src":"wikipedia"},"highlights":[],"references":[{"n":1,"text":"Distance calculated using Microsoft MapPoint mapping software.","url":""},{"n":2,"text":"Williams, Susan (October 19, 2003). \"Road with a view\". Sunday Gazette-Mail. Charleston Gazette. p. 6B.","url":""}],"routeLine":[[38.3067,-80.09436],[38.30669,-80.09537],[38.30665,-80.09611],[38.30651,-80.09692],[38.30617,-80.09777],[38.30569,-80.09853],[38.30492,-80.09977],[38.30456,-80.10065],[38.30439,-80.10153],[38.30436,-80.10229],[38.30448,-80.10317],[38.30465,-80.10397],[38.30485,-80.10505],[38.30497,-80.10596],[38.30497,-80.1069],[38.3048,-80.10866],[38.30471,-80.10958],[38.30481,-80.11052],[38.30562,-80.11199],[38.30599,-80.11296],[38.30602,-80.11388],[38.30603,-80.11505],[38.30616,-80.11598],[38.30642,-80.11672],[38.30697,-80.1175],[38.30877,-80.11972],[38.30967,-80.12085],[38.31045,-80.12181],[38.31084,-80.12241],[38.31123,-80.12341],[38.31135,-80.1245],[38.31109,-80.12541],[38.31047,-80.12609],[38.30985,-80.12647],[38.30927,-80.12705],